The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sport

 Saturday, April 09, 2005 

 IN THE CITY

 Viv Richards is expected to attend the third edition of the McDowell Signature Celebrity golf championship to be held in Gurgaon on April 23. The meet is a charity event held in aid of the CHAMPS Foundation, set up by Sunil Gavaskar. This year?s event will see 18-20 teams, informed organisers at the Tollygunge Club. The city is next in line to host the championship.

 Cricket Coaching Centre of Howrah Union will organise an all-India U-17 meet starting from Sunday. Twelve teams will take part.

 Olympia Club-organised Kalipada Das all-Bengal auction bridge tournament will commence from Friday. The tournament carries a total prize money of Rs 1 lakh.

 Suvrajit Saha (9.5) won the 40th State Open chess championship that concluded at Salt Lake Stadium on Friday.

 HOCKEY: Beighton Cup, quarter final league: Punjab Police vs Tamil Nadu XI (CC amp;FC, 1 pm), Army XI vs Bombay XI (Mohammedan Sporting, 3.15 pm), Indian Oil vs Corps of Signals (CC amp;FC, 3.15 pm).

 SOCCER: Five-a-side meet finals: ITC vs FCI (main plate), M.N. Dastur vs Transworld (losers? plate) at Parsee Club from 4 pm.

 TABLE TENNIS: State ranking meet : Finals at B.C.S. academy from 2 pm.




